Saraswati Puja is celebrated on the eve of Basant Panchami, the indication of the arrival of the spring season. Goddess Saraswati , considered the goddess of knowledge and wisdom is worshipped with great devotion and respect in our homes, educational and cultural institutions. . Believed to be the birthday of  Goddess Saraswati, both young and old participate in the celebrations with great enthusiasm. Vidhya Arambha or the ritual of introducing young children to the world of books and learning is undertaken on this day along with the worshipping of books by students. The deity is almost always seen in white or yellow saree and decorated with flowers of the same colour. Sweets, fruits, khichuri are offered to the goddess and then distributed among all bringing an atmosphere of merriment. 

Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a Happy Saraswati Puja . May the Goddess shower divine and choicest blessings on us leading to success and prosperity in our lives.

Makar Sankranti, a festival  dedicated to the Sun God celebrated in January every year, marks the first day of the sun’s transition into the sun sign Capricorn or Makara in Hindi. On this day, people express their gratitude to nature and its abundant resources .  Also known as the ‘festival of kites’, it marks the onset of summer and the six-month-long auspicious period for Hindus known as Uttaarayan, is observed according to the solar cycles. The festival is celebrated as Sukarat in Central India, Bihu in Assam, Pongal in Tamil Nadu and Makar Sankranti in Bengal, Bihar, Odisha and the neighbouring regions. Various spiritual practices are observed like taking a holy dip in rivers like Kaveri and Ganga, since it is generally believed that doing so would absolve them of their past sins. People also celebrate the occasion with sweets made of jaggery and sesame as well as rice, along with sumptuous meals. 

Therefore, ISTE NIT Durgapur, wishes everyone a Happy Makarsankranti praying that  may the Sun God  fill our lives and homes with sunshine and happiness.
